    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 7000 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - AIR INTAKES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="REMOVE" graphiccount="1">
        <title>AIR INTAKES</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Air Intakes - Remove</title>
            <para>The Air Intake assembly is located on the drivers side of the front hood/fender assembly. The air
                intake grille assembly is a removable item (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900737">Figure 37, Item 2</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the upper and lower four mounting screws.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the four mounting screws and remove the air inlet grille assembly.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Air Intakes - Install</title>
            <figure id="f0900737" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900737.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Air Inlet Grille Mounting</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GRILLE MOUNTING FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. AIR INLET GRILLE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. GRILLE MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. GRILLE SCREW MOUNTING HOLES</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the grille assembly and place into the air inlet frame (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900737">Figure 37, Item 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the grille assembly mounting holes with the air frame assembly mounting tabs.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the four mounting screws and tighten.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
